      • getOriginalIdentifier

        @NonNull
public String getOriginalIdentifier()
        Description copied from interface: IEntityItem
        Get the identifier originally assigned to this entity.

        If the identifier value was reassigned, the return value of this method will be different than value returned by IEntityItem.getIdentifier(). In such cases, a call to IEntityItem.isIdentifierReassigned() is expected to return true.

        If the value was not reassigned, the return value of this method will be the same value returned by IEntityItem.getIdentifier(). In this case, IEntityItem.isIdentifierReassigned() is expected to return false.

        Specified by:
        getOriginalIdentifier in interface IEntityItem
        Returns:
        the original identifier value before reassignment
